I see the issue now. Looking at the spec example more carefully (lines 188-193):

"Newcomer with a cursed sword: premium165 G:100 G base + 50 G curse + 10 G first insurance = 160 G + 5 G fee"

The modifiers from above line apply in this order:
1. Item modifiers (cursed, high-enchantment) apply to base premium
2. First insurance surcharge (10%) applies ON TOP of that (calculated on base+item modifiers)
3. Processing fee (5 G) added at the end

But for follow-up contracts, the 15% discount applies instead of the 10% surcharge, and also applies to the base+item modifiers.
